headlines.description: — Joel Embiid doesn't need to emulate any other NBA star.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid ties career high with 50 points, 76ers beat Magic

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma missed a 3-pointer in the final seconds, and he could accept that.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets hold off Wizards' rally, beat Washington 119-118

headlines.description: — After leading Atlanta to back-to-back wins for the first time in almost two months, Trae Young wasn't ready to say the Hawks have regained last season's winning formula.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's scoring surge sends Hawks past Timberwolves, 134-122

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had a triple-double with 15 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists to lead the Charlotte Hornets to a 111-102 victory over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball's triple-double carries Hornets past Celtics, 111-102

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — The leading scorer had just been placed in the NBA's health and safety protocols. The point guard is out for personal reasons. The team leader got ejected just before halftime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Heat pull away late, top Trail Blazers 104-92

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan understood the Chicago Bulls needed a win in a big way. A huge run to end the game made it happen.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Vucevic lead way as Bulls hold off Cavs 117-104

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 33 points and 15 rebounds, and Khris Middleton scored 27 to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 126-114 victory over the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis leads Bucks past short-handed Grizzlies, 126-114

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored a season-high 41 points, including a clutch 3-pointer with 1:01 to play, and tied his season best with 14 rebounds as the surging Dallas Mavericks held off the Toronto Raptors 102-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic leads streaking Mavericks to 102-98 win over Raptors

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 23 points, 14 assists and 10 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs made 15 3-pointers as they rolled past the Oklahoma City Thunder 118-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray has triple-double as Spurs roll past Thunder, 118-96

headlines.description: — Garrison Mathews scored 23 points, including five 3-pointers, to send the Houston Rockets to a 116-111 victory over the scuffling Utah Jazz on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathews scores 23, Rockets rally past scuffling Jazz 116-111

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 49 points, 14 rebounds and fed Aaron Gordon for a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 1.9 seconds left in overtime for his 10th assist, giving the Denver Nuggets a 130-128 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 49, triple-double as Nuggets edge Clippers in OT

headlines.description: — Cory Joseph made a 14-foot jumper with 25.9 seconds remaining to cap a game-ending 11-0 run that rallied the Detroit Pistons past the Sacramento Kings 133-131 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joseph hits winner, Pistons rally late to stun Kings 133-131

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored a franchise-record 22 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter, Malcolm Brogdon added 19 and the Indiana Pacers increased the pressure on Lakers coach Frank Vogel with a 111-104 victory over Los Angeles on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers roll past Lakers in 4th quarter for skid-stopping win
